Last week, the Verkhovna Rada adopted the draft law 7176, which is titled "On the monitoring of potential threats to national security of Ukraine in the field of economy."
It is strange that essentially the only potential threat to national security of Ukraine in the economic sphere is... the individuals who hold meetings as members of the supervisory board of state-owned companies and state banks.
The initiators of the draft law believe that the decisions made by the supervisory board of the state-owned company in hypothetical Kyiv can somehow solve the national security problems of Ukraine.
We are aware of a large number of new dangers for state-owned companies, but so far there is no information about any company that has needed to physically conduct a supervisory board meeting at its location.
The potential threat from such a law is clear - it provides a great basis for "destroying" all the achievements in the difficult reform of state-owned enterprises after the Revolution of Dignity, including independent supervisory boards, and then establishing manual control.
That which was before the year 2015.
Why do state-owned companies need supervisory boards and who should be included in them?
Moreover, if one harmful bill "flies off" under patriotic slogans, then others may fly off tomorrow - for example, the ProZorro public procurement system or the independence of the National Bank of Ukraine.
